<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="trans-numknown" xml:lang="en">
    <head>Numbers/numerals of Known Value</head>
    <p><!-- gloss --></p>
    <p><specList>
            <specDesc key="num"/>
        </specList>
        <!--<listRef>
            <ptr target="a"/>
            </listRef>--></p>

    <p>The numeral should be placed inside a <gi>num</gi> and given an appropriate
            <att>value</att>, e.g. "8", "42", etc. If it is a particular kind of numeral,
        e.g. acrophonic, it can be given a <att>type</att> with a value of
        "acrophonic".</p>

    <cit>
        <quote><hi rend="supraline">XII</hi></quote>
        <bibl corresp="#ddbdp"/>
        <!-- etc. -->
    </cit>

    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" corresp="#panciera" xml:lang="la">
        <num value="12">XII</num>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"
        corresp="http://insaph.kcl.ac.uk/iaph2007/iAph080058.html#6-1" xml:lang="grc"
        rend="london ddbdp">
        <num value="12">ιβ</num>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london" corresp="http://inslib.kcl.ac.uk/irt2009/IRT022.html">
        <num value="24">XXIIII</num>
    </egXML>
    
    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples" rend="london" corresp="http://papyri.info/ddbdp/bgu;1;10#8">
        <num value="54">νδ</num>
    </egXML>
